#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:42
msgid ""
"**QGIS**: Can you tell us a bit about yourself? What\\'s your educational"
" background? What did you do before joining the data visualization team "
"at FT?"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:44
msgid "![](../images/ft_gotthard-tunnel.png)"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:46
msgid "*Example: Gotthard rail and road tunnel in the Swiss Alps.*"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:48
msgid ""
"**Steven**: I am traditionally trained as scientific illustrator. What's "
"that I hear you ask? It involves producing illustrations for medical "
"journals, natural history publications anything where you are trying to "
"convey information visually where a photograph can't. Think of diagrams "
"showing the human circulatory system, or showing a procedure to fix a "
"broken bone. Sadly there wasn't much call for that kind of work when I "
"left university and I basically fell into the job at the FT. I have "
"always been good at maths, which I think is important when working with "
"data visualisations, it has certainly helped me with my coding as well."
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:50
msgid "**QGIS**: How did you discover QGIS?"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:52
msgid ""
"**Steven**: I came across QGIS in 2013 when we were working on a [project"
" mapping the ethnicity of the Middle "
"East](http://ig.ft.com/features/2013-07-19_middleeast_religion_map/dist/index.html)"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:54
msgid ""
"We used it to georeference maps that were created by a professor at "
"Columbia University. At first I found it really tricky using the add "
"feature drawing tool, probably because it was unlike anything I'd used in"
" Adobe Illustrator for 17 years prior! I also found it frustrating that "
"you had to save things twice, once when done editing the shapefile, then "
"again to save the project. However, this was just down to inexperience "
"with the program and in the end it did exactly what we needed, which was "
"to produce shapefiles that we could add to a Mapbox base map."
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:56
msgid "**QGIS**: What\\'s the role of QGIS within your usual workflows?"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:58
#, python-format
msgid ""
"**Steven**: QGIS is now an integral part of our mapping workflow. I don't"
" use any other GIS tool to create our maps. Although a few members of our"
" team also use Map Publisher as they feel more comfortable staying within"
" Adobe Illustrator. I would say 80% of our maps are now produced in QGIS."
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:60
msgid "![](../images/ft_blm-federal-land-map.png)"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:62
