#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:88
msgid ""
"**QGIS**: Can you describe the strengths and weaknesses of QGIS regarding"
" the tasks you have to do?"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:90
msgid ""
"**Steven**: When I first used QGIS I saw it as a specialist tool, fit for"
" only dealing with specific tasks. I really didn't see it a production "
"tool. In late 2014 two of my colleagues went on a QGIS course held by "
"Alasdair Rae at Sheffield University. They both enthused about how good "
"QGIS was, so I took it upon myself to evaluate it as a tool that could be"
" used to produce all our maps."
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:92
msgid ""
"Within about two weeks I was convinced that it would be viable. The main "
"selling point was the ability to set up style guides for everything "
"including zoom level styling for street-level maps."
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:94
msgid ""
"I have a system set up where we have sets of Google sheets with columns "
"for name, lat, long, marker-icon, fontweight, fontsize and whether you "
"want the marker visible or not."
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:96
msgid ""
"The marker icon is a dropdown connected to a vLookUp table which fills in"
" all the details for that marker."
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:98
#, python-format
msgid ""
"So all I have to do is download the csv, import it into QGIS, apply a "
"style and I have a map that is 95% ready to go."
msgstr ""

#: content/project/case-studies/qgis_at_financial_times.md:100
msgid ""
"To be perfectly honest I can't think of any weaknesses, there are a "
"couple of things that I would like to see or be able to do but, I don't "
"see that as a weakness, just a missing feature."
msgstr ""

